    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-5">Summary Checklist for Filling a 4x8 Bed</h2>
    <p>Follow this actionable checklist to fill your bed perfectly:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Determine Depth:</strong> Measure the inside depth of your 4x8 frame.</li>
      <li><strong>Calculate Volume:</strong> Use the chart above (e.g., 32 cubic feet for 12 inches deep).</li>
      <li><strong>Determine Bag vs. Bulk:</strong> Buy bags if volume is &lt; 20 cu ft; buy bulk delivery if volume is &gt; 20 cu ft.</li>
      <li><strong>Layer the Bottom:</strong> If the bed is deep (18+ inches), add logs, sticks, or grass clippings at the bottom to save money on soil (this is called "Hugelkultur").</li>
      <li><strong>Fill the Soil:</strong> Add your raised bed soil mix to within 1–2 inches of the top.</li>
      <li><strong>Water Deeply:</strong> Soak the new soil thoroughly. It will settle, and you may need to add a few more bags to top it off before planting.</li>
    </ol>

